basisset.dc:title: U500
basisset.dc:description: That basis set is universal, i.e. the same uncontracted array of exponents is used for every atom. The exponents are integer powers of 2; the following ranges were chosen for each function type: s: 2^27 ... 2^-9 p: 2^26 ... 2^-9 d: 2^17 ... 2^-6 f: 2^12 ... 2^-4 g: 2^4 ... 2^-3 h: 2^1 ... 2^-2 The choice was based on the scalar-relativistic calculations of a few monoatomic species (neutral and ionized He, B, N, Ne, Ca and others) at CCSD(T,Full) or BD(T,Full) level of theory and some larger species (H2O, W2, AuH, AuB, PtH(-), PuO2(2+), Sg2 and others) with various DFT functionals using Gaussian 09W software.
